Subject: Can we delete files in FSAA folder for decomm'd Netapp
Description: Need assistance verifying files we have in folder D:FSAADA6PNETAPP1B (DA6PNETAPP1B is an Netapp filer that is decommissioned). Looking to clear up space.
Solution_Comment__c:
[Issue]
Customer was looking to remove an old host folder in the FSAA directory

[Resolution]
If the host has been decommissioned and will no longer we scanned, then it is fine to delete that folder. In this case, the customer realized it was an alias for an active server and opted to leave it as is.
